My dad started collecting Kentucky bourbon in 2017. In 2019 I got involved in attempt to find a Pappy Van Winkle, which was his dream bottle at the time. I found one, and the hunt got me just as hooked as he was. For the last 4 years we have had a great time searching for bourbons, talking about it, going to distilleries, and waiting in long lines in the cold for rare releases. The collection is constantly growing, but I save some of my best finds of the year to bring out on Christmas. This year was the best. Keeping this one a secret for several months wasn’t easy, and I’m still in shock that I was able to get it and that it’s part of the collection now. After unwrapping some smaller bottles first, the final was this - perhaps the most iconic bottle in all of bourbon - Old Rip Van Winkle 25 Year. We will keep collecting, but it probably won’t get any bigger than this 😊
